    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-03T16:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-03T16:36:00-05:00" n="242"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d242">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">814.51/309: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-03T15:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 3, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received November 5, 9.15 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Strictly confidential. Department’s October 25, 7 [<hi rend="italic">6</hi>]
                    p.m., my October 30, noon.<note n="12" xml:id="d242fn12">Latter not
                        printed.</note> President Cabrera informed me during an interview this
                    morning that Professor Kemmerer’s report was being translated, but he did not
                    intimate that it would be made public.</p>
                <pb facs="0369" n="284" xml:id="pg_284"/>
                <p>He further stated that he would instruct Minister Mendez to request the
                    Department to make such use of this report as might appear desirable.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
